            <title><![CDATA[The head of the world&#8217;s coolest innovation lab wants to focus on . . . public policy]]></title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;Dava Newman, the new head of MIT&amp;#x2019;s Media Lab, wants the lab to take on bigger problems and reach out into the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If Willy Wonka had microchips, his factory would have been the MIT Media Lab. The 500-person facility actually houses 25 different research groups, which are known for creating some of the most wondrous marvels of our era&amp;#x2014;from &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fastcompany.com/1669799/mit-creates-amazing-ui-from-levitating-orbs&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;computers you control with levitating orbs&lt;/a&gt;&amp;#xA0;to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fastcompany.com/1672770/how-mit-is-hacking-thousands-of-worms-to-print-buildings&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;architecture woven by silk worms&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fastcompany.com/90669988/the-head-of-the-worlds-coolest-innovation-lab-wants-to-focus-onpublic-policy?partner=rss&amp;amp;utm_source=feedburner&amp;amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=feedburner+fastcompany&amp;amp;utm_content=feedburner&quot;&gt;Read Full Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/fastcodesign/feed/~4/ZI8xFbB8gTg&quot; height=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;/&gt;</description>
