            <title><![CDATA[Meet the Nigerian designer beloved by Madonna and Lupita Nyong&#8217;o]]></title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;Busayo Olupona combines traditional Nigerian prints with Western silhouettes. Over the last two years, her brand has exploded as consumers are eager to celebrate African design. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Busayo Olupona didn&amp;#x2019;t always love the vibrant clothes of her native Nigeria. When she moved from Lagos to California, she showed up for her first day of middle school in a colorful, patterned Nigerian dress only to be ridiculed mercilessly by her white classmates.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fastcompany.com/90668849/meet-the-nigerian-designer-beloved-by-madonna-and-lupita-nyongo?partner=rss&amp;amp;utm_source=feedburner&amp;amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=feedburner+fastcompany&amp;amp;utm_content=feedburner&quot;&gt;Read Full Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/fastcodesign/feed/~4/Y7sv-c4w6WI&quot; height=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;/&gt;</description>
